**Master-slave architecture**
--> master-slave architecture or controller-agent is used to distribute the workload of jenkins
1. master (controller)
--> the jenkins master is the main jenkins server.
--> it manage jenkins configuration
--> create and schedule jobs
--> store plugins and job details
--> decide where a job should run

2. slave (worker/build-agent)
--> a slave/agent is another machine connected to jenkins that actually runs the jobs.
--> it execute build steps
--> it run test
--> deploy code


